VALUES ('c7c1f3ea-8dcd-4e40-8806-d0e166a9ed89', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'During the Great Depression, many families could no longer afford store-bought goods. To stretch their budgets, they mended worn clothing and reused materials whenever possible. ______ flour companies began printing their sacks in colorful patterns so the cloth could be sewn into dresses.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"Recognizing this,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: it links the companies'' action to their awareness of families reusing materials."},{"id":"B","text":"In contrast,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the companies'' action supports the trend of reuse rather than opposing it."},{"id":"C","text":"Even so,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: ''Even so'' signals a concession, but the final sentence flows naturally from the prior idea."},{"id":"D","text":"By coincidence,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the companies acted deliberately because of the reuse trend, not by chance."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Identify the behavior
The text says families {{yellow:reused materials whenever possible}}, and companies responded to that habit.
Step 2 — Choose the responsive transition
Because the companies acted with awareness of the reuse trend, ''Recognizing this'' connects the cause to their response.
Distractor analysis:
- B: ''In contrast'' needs opposition, but the action supports reuse.
- C: ''Even so'' signals concession that is not present.
- D: ''By coincidence'' implies chance, but the action was deliberate.', 'Did the companies print patterns because they knew people were reusing the sacks?', 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'easy', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
